HAI burden (Germany, PPS 2011) with uncertainty and YLL/YLD

Source: R/data-docs.R
hai_germany_2011.Rd

Format

A tibble with 6 rows and 16 variables:

type

HAI type or "All".

cases, deaths, dalys, yll, yld

Point estimates (integers).

cases_lo, cases_hi

95\ deaths_lo, deaths_hi95\ dalys_lo, dalys_hi95\ yll_lo, yll_hi95\ yld_lo, yld_hi95\Zacher et al. (2019), Euro Surveill 24(46):1900135.hai_germany_2011Point estimates and 95% uncertainty intervals for annual cases, attributable deaths, total dalys, and the DALY components yll (years of life lost) and yld (years lived with disability) for five healthcare-associated infections (HAP, UTI, BSI, SSI, CDI), plus a total row "All".An attribute dalys_per_100k_total gives total DALYs per 100,000 population (Germany total: 308.2).datasets
